description:
{handcrafting the pendant}
i took my sterling scrap heated it until it was cherry red hot. kept heating it until it formed a ball and once it had cooled i hammered it flat. i let it take its own shape. i then used a fine grit sanding stick and sanded the top of the disk to give it a matte finish. the sides and back i hit with the torch to give it a patina finish. i love sides and back just as much.

